WEBVTT

00:03.950 --> 00:05.577
Hello.

00:05.619 --> 00:06.916
Hey, Brandon.

00:06.953 --> 00:08.580
oh, my God,
the lonesome traveler.

00:08.622 --> 00:09.748
Hey. Welcome home.

00:09.790 --> 00:11.087
-Thank you, my man.
-Good to see you.

00:11.124 --> 00:12.250
-Good to be seen.
-Hey.

00:12.359 --> 00:13.656
-How are you, bro?
-How's the 'Stang?

00:13.693 --> 00:14.991
Those rednecks treat you okay?

00:15.028 --> 00:16.256
They ever find that water pump?

00:16.363 --> 00:17.830
Yeah, they did find
the water pump,

00:17.864 --> 00:19.491
and it's, uh, running just
fine. Thank you very much.

00:19.533 --> 00:22.764
Well, you should have done
what l did-- buy a new corvette.

00:22.803 --> 00:24.065
You bought a new 'Vette?

00:24.104 --> 00:25.366
-You know it.
-collectors edition?

00:25.405 --> 00:26.565
-Hello?
-Nice.

00:26.606 --> 00:27.800
clare, come on.

00:27.841 --> 00:29.433
l'm coming.
l'm coming.

00:29.476 --> 00:31.273
Dude, you know
what this weekend is?

00:31.311 --> 00:33.211
lt's reunion weekend
at the beach club.

00:33.246 --> 00:35.373
Better go dig that green
sweatshirt out of your closet.

00:35.415 --> 00:36.882
No, l don't...
l don't think so.

00:36.917 --> 00:39.249
l got a lot of road dust
to knock off myself.

00:39.286 --> 00:41.015
You might want to reconsider.

00:41.054 --> 00:43.249
This year's bikini stock
is pretty high.

00:43.290 --> 00:44.621
What's the matter, Brandon?

00:44.658 --> 00:46.626
You don't want to sit
in the boiling hot sun

00:46.660 --> 00:48.252
and listen to all the stories

00:48.295 --> 00:50.263
about the beach nymphs
Steve used to fantasize about?

00:50.297 --> 00:52.765
Well, that's quite an offer,
Mr. and Mrs. Bickerson,

00:52.799 --> 00:55.768
but l think l may pass, at
least for the time being.

00:55.802 --> 00:57.394
Well, look what
the wind blew in.

00:57.437 --> 00:58.563
-See ya, Val.
-Bye.

00:58.605 --> 01:00.129
-Have fun. Hi.
-Val.

01:00.173 --> 01:01.299
How are you?

01:01.341 --> 01:02.968
Have you been
holding down the fort?

01:03.009 --> 01:04.635
Yes, sir. l am proud to report

01:04.678 --> 01:07.374
that while you were out
on your scout, l was able

01:07.414 --> 01:09.848
to fend off a leaky toilet and
an air-conditioning breakdown.

01:09.883 --> 01:11.510
Hmm. Natives were restless?

01:11.551 --> 01:12.984
-Mm.
-Why are you all dressed up?

01:13.019 --> 01:14.486
l have a meeting with a cPA.

01:14.521 --> 01:15.647
Hoping to get a loan.

01:15.689 --> 01:16.917
oh, yeah. Right.

01:16.957 --> 01:18.481
Kenny Bannerman.
You know him?

01:18.525 --> 01:20.857
Bannerman. Kenny Bannerman.

01:20.894 --> 01:22.418
Yeah, yeah.

01:22.462 --> 01:24.453
He used to work
with my dad, right?

01:24.498 --> 01:26.523
Yeah, Dad said he was one
of the brightest young cPAs

01:26.566 --> 01:27.692
he ever worked with.

01:27.734 --> 01:29.429
Well, l hope so.
l need some extra cash,

01:29.469 --> 01:31.960
or the After Dark's not gonna
be able to turn on its lights.

01:32.005 --> 01:34.132
Well, they do call it
the After Dark.

01:34.174 --> 01:35.641
l'm sorry your summer

01:35.675 --> 01:36.699
didn't go so well.

01:36.743 --> 01:38.142
Yeah, me, too.

01:38.178 --> 01:39.440
l will see you later.

01:39.479 --> 01:40.605
Good luck.

01:40.647 --> 01:43.013
Thanks.

01:48.422 --> 01:51.687
The more things change,
the more they stay the same.

